---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Contact from '../../components/Contact.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import background from '../../assets/background.svg';
---

<Layout
    title="Rise Global Text Update | Zach Hunter"
    description="Deterministic rename and text-governance workflow for Rise courses, including alt text updates, batch CSV replacement, and QA reporting."
>
    <img id="background" src={background.src} alt="" fetchpriority="high" />
    <main>
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Rise Global Text Update</h1>
            <p class="lead">Apply exact-match global text updates across exported Rise courses, including image alt text, and generate replacement reports to support reliable, consistent QA review.</p>
            <input type="hidden" id="xapiFunctionUrl" value={import.meta.env.PUBLIC_XAPI_FUNCTION_URL ?? ''} />

            <div class="accordion">
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <h2 class="accordion-header">
                        <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" id="caseStudyToggle">
                            Design Approach
                        </button>
                    </h2>
                    <div id="collapseCaseStudy" class="accordion-content">
                        <div class="accordion-body">
                            <h5>Overview</h5>
                            <p>This tool was designed as a scalable content update workflow for Rise courses. It enables exact-match global text replacement using exported XLIFF files, including both visible content and image alt text, and generates replacement reports to support review before republishing.</p>

                            <h5>The Operational Challenge</h5>
                            <p>Coordinated text updates across dozens or hundreds of courses are time-consuming and error-prone when handled manually. Hidden blocks such as accordions and accessibility fields make it easy to miss instances. During high-change release cycles, teams also need reliable counts to validate that updates were applied consistently.</p>
                            <p>AI-assisted discovery can help surface content, but it does not guarantee predictable counts or exact control when precision matters.</p>

                            <h5>Design Decisions</h5>
                            <p><strong>Exact-Match Replacement</strong><br>The workflow prioritizes exact-match updates over probabilistic or AI-driven approaches. The same input produces the same output, enabling predictable results and confident QA validation.</p>
                            <p><strong>Accessibility Awareness</strong><br>Image alt text is included in the replacement process to prevent terminology drift in accessibility fields, an area often overlooked during manual review.</p>
                            <p><strong>Local-First Processing</strong><br>All file processing occurs in the browser. Course content never leaves the user's machine. This reduces privacy risk and allows the tool to function offline once loaded.</p>

                            <h5>Performance Impact</h5>
                            <p>Manual updates that might otherwise require hours of repetitive editing are converted into a structured export-scan-import process that can be completed in minutes per course. Replacement counts provide visibility before republishing, reducing QA risk during release cycles.</p>

                            <h5>Implementation Details</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Applies exact-match global replacement across exported Rise content</li>
                                <li>Updates both visible text and image alt text</li>
                                <li>Supports bulk update pairs via CSV import</li>
                                <li>Lints common Unicode substitutions such as quotes and hyphens</li>
                                <li>Preserves XML structure and special characters</li>
                                <li>Safely replaces <code>&lt;source&gt;</code> tags with <code>&lt;target&gt;</code> tags</li>
                                <li>Generates downloadable replacement reports</li>
                            </ul>

                            <h5>Privacy and Data Handling</h5>
                            <ul>
                                <li>All file processing occurs entirely in the browser</li>
                                <li>No course data is transmitted to a server</li>
                                <li>Works offline after initial load</li>
                                <li>Only anonymous usage metrics are collected</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="quick-start">
                <h2 class="quick-start-heading">Quick Start</h2>
                <p class="quick-start-note">This tool edits an exported XLIFF file. You will need to re-import it into Rise and republish for changes to take effect. Back up your course first using Snapshots or Duplicate.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Open your course in Articulate Rise, go to <strong>Settings &gt; Translations</strong>, and select <strong>Export XLIFF file</strong>.</li>
                    <li>Open this tool and upload the exported <code>.xlf</code> file.</li>
                    <li>Add pairs of <em>original text</em> and <em>replacement text</em> to apply across the course.</li>
                    <li>Choose <strong>Process XLIFF</strong>. The tool will apply your changes and show a summary of which replacements were made.</li>
                    <li>Download the processed XLIFF file. Optionally, download a CSV log of the results for your own records or reporting.</li>
                    <li>Go to <strong>Settings &gt; Translations</strong> in your Rise course and click <strong>Import translated text</strong>. Upload your modified file.</li>
                    <li>Review your updated course content and re-publish to make the changes live.</li>
                </ol>
            </div>
            
            <form id="xliffForm">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="xliffFile">Select XLIFF File:</label>
                    <input type="file" id="xliffFile" accept=".xlf,.xliff">
                </div>
                
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label>Text Replacements:</label>
                    <div id="replacements">
                        <div class="replacement-row">
                            <input type="text" class="original" placeholder="Original Text" aria-label="Original text to replace">
                            <input type="text" class="replacement" placeholder="Replacement Text" aria-label="New replacement text">
                            <button type="button" class="btn-remove" aria-label="Remove this replacement pair">×</button>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="button-group compact">
                        <button type="button" class="btn secondary" id="addReplacement">Add Replacement</button>
                        <button type="button" class="btn outline" id="importCSV">Import CSV</button>
                        <input type="file" id="csvFile" accept=".csv,.txt" aria-label="Import replacements from CSV file" style="display: none;">
                    </div>
                    <p class="csv-hint">CSV format: <code>original text, replacement text</code> (one pair per line). Use quotes for values containing commas. <a href="/sample-replacements.csv" download>Download sample CSV</a></p>
                </div>
                
                <button type="submit" class="btn primary">
                    Process XLIFF
                    <span class="spinner" id="spinner"></span>
                </button>
                <p id="statusMessage" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p>
            </form>
            
            <div id="results">
                <h3>Processing Results</h3>
                <div id="replacementSummary"></div>
                <div class="button-group compact">
                    <a id="downloadLink" class="btn success" download="processed.xlf">Download Processed File</a>
                    <a id="downloadReportLink" class="btn outline" download="report.csv">Download Report CSV</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <Contact />
        <Footer />
    </main>
</Layout>

<script>
    import { parseCSVLine, processXliff, toCsvField } from '../../scripts/xliff-tool.js';

    type ReplacementPair = [string, string];
    type ReplacementCounts = Record<string, number>;

    // Function to log xAPI usage data
    async function logXapiUsage(replacementsChecked: number, totalReplacements: number) {
        try {
            const payload = {
                replacementsChecked,
                totalReplacements
            };
            
            // Use relative URL in development to avoid CORS issues
            const isLocalhost = window.location.hostname === "localhost" || window.location.hostname === "127.0.0.1";
            const configuredApiUrl = (document.getElementById('xapiFunctionUrl') as HTMLInputElement | null)?.value;
            const apiUrl = isLocalhost 
                ? "/.netlify/functions/send-xapi"  // Use relative URL for local development
                : (configuredApiUrl || "/.netlify/functions/send-xapi");
                
            const response = await fetch(apiUrl, {
                method: "POST",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                body: JSON.stringify(payload)
            });
            
            if (response.ok) {
            } else {
                console.warn("xAPI request failed with status:", response.status);
            }
        } catch (err) {
            console.warn("xAPI logging failed:", err);
        }
    }
    
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        try {
            // Initialize UI elements
            const caseStudyToggle = document.getElementById('caseStudyToggle');
            const collapseCaseStudy = document.getElementById('collapseCaseStudy');
            const resultsSection = document.getElementById('results');
            const spinner = document.getElementById('spinner');
            const addReplacementBtn = document.getElementById('addReplacement');
            const importCSVBtn = document.getElementById('importCSV');
            const csvFileInput = document.getElementById('csvFile') as HTMLInputElement | null;
            const xliffForm = document.getElementById('xliffForm');
            const replacementsContainer = document.getElementById('replacements');
            const statusMessage = document.getElementById('statusMessage');

            function setStatus(message: string, isError = false) {
                if (!statusMessage) return;
                statusMessage.textContent = message;
                statusMessage.style.color = isError ? '#b91c1c' : '#047857';
            }

            function escapeHtml(value: string) {
                return value
                    .replace(/&/g, '&amp;')
                    .replace(/</g, '&lt;')
                    .replace(/>/g, '&gt;')
                    .replace(/"/g, '&quot;')
                    .replace(/'/g, '&#39;');
            }
            
            // Hide results initially
            if (resultsSection) resultsSection.style.display = 'none';
            
            // Function to create a new empty replacement row
            function createEmptyRow() {
                const row = document.createElement('div');
                row.className = 'replacement-row';
                
                const originalInput = document.createElement('input');
                originalInput.type = 'text';
                originalInput.className = 'original';
                originalInput.placeholder = 'Original Text';
                originalInput.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Original text to replace');
                
                const replacementInput = document.createElement('input');
                replacementInput.type = 'text';
                replacementInput.className = 'replacement';
                replacementInput.placeholder = 'Replacement Text';
                replacementInput.setAttribute('aria-label', 'New replacement text');
                
                const removeBtn = document.createElement('button');
                removeBtn.type = 'button';
                removeBtn.className = 'btn-remove';
                removeBtn.textContent = '×';
                removeBtn.setAttribute('aria-label', 'Remove this replacement pair');
                
                removeBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    if (!replacementsContainer) return;
                    if (replacementsContainer.querySelectorAll('.replacement-row').length > 1) {
                        row.remove();
                    } else {
                        originalInput.value = '';
                        replacementInput.value = '';
                    }
                });
                
                row.appendChild(originalInput);
                row.appendChild(replacementInput);
                row.appendChild(removeBtn);
                
                return row;
            }
            
            // Helper function to create a replacement row with values
            function createReplacementRow(original: string, replacement: string) {
                const row = createEmptyRow();
                
                if (original) {
                    const originalInput = row.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('.original');
                    if (originalInput) originalInput.value = original;
                }
                
                if (replacement) {
                    const replacementInput = row.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('.replacement');
                    if (replacementInput) replacementInput.value = replacement;
                }
                
                return row;
            }
            
            // Helper function to collect replacements from the form
            function collectReplacements() {
                const replacements: ReplacementPair[] = [];
                document.querySelectorAll('.replacement-row').forEach(row => {
                    const originalInput = row.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('.original');
                    const replacementInput = row.querySelector<HTMLInputElement>('.replacement');
                    
                    if (originalInput && replacementInput) {
                        const original = originalInput.value ? originalInput.value.trim() : '';
                        const replacement = replacementInput.value ? replacementInput.value.trim() : '';
                        
                        if (original && replacement) {
                            replacements.push([original, replacement]);
                        }
                    }
                });
                return replacements;
            }
            
            // Helper function to create object URLs and track them for cleanup
            const objectUrls: string[] = [];
            function createObjectURL(blob: Blob) {
                const url = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
                objectUrls.push(url);
                return url;
            }
            
            // Clean up object URLs when page unloads
            window.addEventListener('beforeunload', () => {
                objectUrls.forEach(url => URL.revokeObjectURL(url));
            });
            
            // Initialize accordion
            if (caseStudyToggle && collapseCaseStudy) {
                caseStudyToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    const isCollapsed = caseStudyToggle.classList.contains('collapsed');
                    caseStudyToggle.classList.toggle('collapsed');
                    collapseCaseStudy.style.display = isCollapsed ? 'block' : 'none';
                });
            }
            
            // Add replacement row button
            if (addReplacementBtn && replacementsContainer) {
                addReplacementBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
                    replacementsContainer.appendChild(createEmptyRow());
                });
            }
            
            // Import CSV functionality
            if (importCSVBtn && csvFileInput) {
                importCSVBtn.addEventListener('click', () => csvFileInput.click());
                
                csvFileInput.addEventListener('change', (event) => {
                    try {
                        const input = event.target as HTMLInputElement | null;
                        if (!input) return;
                        const file = input.files && input.files[0];
                        if (!file) return;
                        
                        const reader = new FileReader();
                        reader.onload = (e) => {
                            try {
                                const fileReader = e.target as FileReader | null;
                                if (!fileReader) return;
                                const content = fileReader.result;
                                if (!content) return;
                                
                                const lines = content.toString().split(/\r?\n/);
                                if (!replacementsContainer) return;
                                
                                replacementsContainer.innerHTML = '';
                                
                                lines.forEach((line, index) => {
                                    if (!line.trim()) return;

                                    const parts = parseCSVLine(line);
                                    if (parts.length < 2) return;

                                    // Allow a conventional header row.
                                    if (index === 0 && parts[0].toLowerCase() === 'original text' && parts[1].toLowerCase() === 'replacement text') return;

                                    const original = parts[0];
                                    const replacement = parts[1];

                                    if (original && replacement) {
                                        replacementsContainer.appendChild(createReplacementRow(original, replacement));
                                    }
                                });

                                if (!replacementsContainer.querySelector('.replacement-row')) {
                                    replacementsContainer.appendChild(createEmptyRow());
                                }
                            } catch (error) {
                                console.error('Error processing CSV:', error);
                                setStatus('Error processing CSV file. Please check the format.', true);
                            }
                        };
                        reader.onerror = () => setStatus('Error reading the CSV file.', true);
                        reader.readAsText(file);
                    } catch (error) {
                        console.error('Error handling CSV file:', error);
                    }
                });
            }
            
            // Form submission
            if (xliffForm) {
                xliffForm.addEventListener('submit', (event) => {
                    event.preventDefault();
                    
                    try {
                        const fileInput = document.getElementById('xliffFile') as HTMLInputElement | null;
                        if (!fileInput) return;
                        
                        const file = fileInput.files && fileInput.files[0];
                        if (!file) {
                            setStatus('Please select an XLIFF file.', true);
                            return;
                        }
                        
                        // Show spinner
                        if (spinner) spinner.style.display = 'inline-block';
                        
                        // Collect replacements
                        const replacements = collectReplacements();

                        if (!replacements.length) {
                            setStatus('Add at least one valid replacement pair before processing.', true);
                            if (spinner) spinner.style.display = 'none';
                            return;
                        }
                        
                        // Read and process the file
                        const reader = new FileReader();
                        reader.onload = (e) => {
                            try {
                                const fileReader = e.target as FileReader | null;
                                if (!fileReader) throw new Error('Could not read file content');
                                const content = fileReader.result;
                                if (!content) throw new Error('Could not read file content');
                                
                                const result = processXliff(content.toString(), replacements);
                                const processedContent = result.content;
                                const replacementCounts = (result.replacementCounts || {}) as ReplacementCounts;
                                
                                // Create download links
                                const downloadLink = document.getElementById('downloadLink') as HTMLAnchorElement | null;
                                if (downloadLink) {
                                    const blob = new Blob([processedContent], { type: 'application/xml' });
                                    downloadLink.href = createObjectURL(blob);
                                    downloadLink.download = file.name.replace('.xlf', '_processed.xlf');
                                }
                                
                                // Calculate totals
                                let totalReplacements = 0;
                                replacements.forEach(([original]) => {
                                    const count = replacementCounts[original] || 0;
                                    totalReplacements += count;
                                });
                                
                                // Create report CSV
                                let reportCSV = 'Original Text,Replacement Text,Replacements Made\n';
                                replacements.forEach(([original, replacement]) => {
                                    reportCSV += `${toCsvField(original)},${toCsvField(replacement)},${replacementCounts[original] || 0}\n`;
                                });
                                reportCSV += `${toCsvField('TOTAL')},${toCsvField(`${replacements.length} patterns`)},${totalReplacements}\n`;
                                
                                const downloadReportLink = document.getElementById('downloadReportLink') as HTMLAnchorElement | null;
                                if (downloadReportLink) {
                                    const reportBlob = new Blob([reportCSV], { type: 'text/csv' });
                                    downloadReportLink.href = createObjectURL(reportBlob);
                                    downloadReportLink.download = 'replacement_report.csv';
                                }
                                
                                // Display summary
                                const replacementSummary = document.getElementById('replacementSummary');
                                if (replacementSummary) {
                                    let summaryHTML = '<table aria-label="Replacement Results Summary"><caption>Text Replacement Summary</caption><thead><tr><th scope="col">Original Text</th><th scope="col">Replacement Text</th><th scope="col">Replacements Made</th></tr></thead><tbody>';
                                    
                                    replacements.forEach(([original, replacement]) => {
                                        summaryHTML += `<tr><td>${escapeHtml(original)}</td><td>${escapeHtml(replacement)}</td><td>${replacementCounts[original] || 0}</td></tr>`;
                                    });
                                    
                                    // Add total row
                                    summaryHTML += `<tr class="total-row"><td colspan="2"><strong>TOTAL (${replacements.length} patterns)</strong></td><td><strong>${totalReplacements}</strong></td></tr>`;
                                    
                                    summaryHTML += '</tbody></table>';
                                    replacementSummary.innerHTML = summaryHTML;
                                }
                                
                                // Show results
                                if (resultsSection) resultsSection.style.display = 'block';
                                setStatus('XLIFF processed successfully.');
                                
                                logXapiUsage(replacements.length, totalReplacements);
                            } catch (error) {
                                console.error('Error processing XLIFF:', error);
                                setStatus('Error processing XLIFF file. Please check the file format.', true);
                            } finally {
                                // Hide spinner
                                if (spinner) spinner.style.display = 'none';
                            }
                        };
                        
                        reader.onerror = () => {
                            setStatus('Error reading the XLIFF file.', true);
                            if (spinner) spinner.style.display = 'none';
                        };
                        
                        reader.readAsText(file);
                    } catch (error) {
                        console.error('Error submitting form:', error);
                        setStatus('An error occurred. Please try again.', true);
                        if (spinner) spinner.style.display = 'none';
                    }
                });
            }
        } catch (error) {
            console.error('Error initializing XLIFF tool:', error);
        }
    });
</script>
